==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cerography
<hw>Ce*rog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>khro`s</grk> wax + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of making characters or designs in, or with,
wax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A method of making stereotype plates from inscribed
sheets of wax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerolite</ent>⟦br⟧
